Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}. Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{6%ounce} into ¼-inch-thick rounds. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Remove and discard any large stems from @kale{4%ounce}.

Place @farro{3/4%cup} and 3½ cups water (6 cups for 4 servings) in a #medium pot{}. Bring to a boil and cook until farro is tender, ~{25-30%minutes}. Drain farro if necessary.

While farro cooks, pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a #large pot{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook, stirring frequently, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pot.

Meanwhile, heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{2%tsp} in the large pot over medium-high heat. Add onion and carrots; season with salt and pepper. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are lightly browned and slightly softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp} and garlic into pot with veggies. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Add @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce can}, @veggie stock concentrate{3}, 3 cups water (6 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer. Cook until carrots are just softened, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Use pot used for chicken here.

Once carrots are just softened, stir in kale. Cook until kale is wilted, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Stir cooked farro into pot. Taste and season generously with salt and pepper.

Once kale is wilted, stir in chicken.

Halve @demi-baguette{1} lengthwise.

Place @butter{2%tbsp} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until just softened, ~{10-15%seconds}. Stir in half the @garlic powder{1%tsp} and season with salt and pepper.

Toast baguette halves, then spread cut sides with garlic butter. Halve each piece on a diagonal.

Divide soup between #bowls{}. Sprinkle with @parmesan cheese{3%tbsp} and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%tsp} to taste. Serve with garlic bread on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.